commit message: Oops, duplicate menu entries. Use the same ID like the md5 sum..
Turns out I have no clue how I do my own hashes. SHA1, not MD5!

Pass '-cols 100000' to w3m so it won't wrap lines, instead of trying to
unwrap lines in a fragile way.

Another trick to get more links: Do a Google search and grep the results for
myspace, wikipedia, etc.

Maybe I should drop the Wikipedia one though, too many non-music results..

Sanity checks for Wikipedia results: Check the page source for a 'musical
artist' infobox to check if at least it's about an artist/band. Gets rid
of a few (nasty) false positives like Yousef -> Ramzi Yousef.

Fix obscure crash bug (loading a schedule without track info with TrackView
set as the default.

Make sure all stars are still visible when there are many web buttons in an
event dialog.
Add SoundCloud links. That service seems pretty neat.

If we have no link types in a schedule, show the URLs instead of unlabeled
buttons.
Translation for the ChooserActivity context menu.

Parse subtitles in Pentabarf schedules.

The rendering is a bit ugly, I have to make the description field a bit more
than just a plaintext field to fix that..

0.9.5.

Push Dutch translations right before Dance Valley, and fix one crash bug
that I already fixed but happened in the wild today. :-(
